────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BOOK DATA — CC BY-SA 4.0
Applies to: books/*/book.json, books/*/waypoints.json
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The waypoints — the coordinates, the passages chosen, the certainty judgements
and the editorial notes — are licensed Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike
4.0 International.

    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Share-alike, deliberately: the dataset is the point of this project, and it
should stay open. Reuse it, build a better interface than ours, but keep it
free.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL — see each book's `rights` block
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The novel, the translation, the transcription and the map imagery are separate
rights objects and are NOT covered by either licence above. Each book records
its own provenance in `books/<slug>/book.json` under `rights`.

We describe the catalogue as rights-reviewed, never as "licence-clean". Public
domain is jurisdiction-specific: a text that is free in the United States may
not be free where you are. Check before you reuse.

Map imagery carries its own terms — the National Library of Scotland's
historical layers are CC BY-NC-SA (non-commercial), and OpenStreetMap data is
ODbL. Attribution is displayed on the map, and must remain so.
